        <definition>uint8_t* http_response::body_frag_start</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>body_frag_start</name>
        <qualifiedname>http_response::body_frag_start</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Start address of the body fragment contained in the recv_buf. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><verbatim>                  recv_buffer that contains header + body
                  _______________________________________

                              |←-------- body_frag_len ---------→|
           |←--------------------- data len --------------------→|
       ---------------------------------------------------------------
 ..header  |      header      |               body               |  body..
       ---------------------------------------------------------------
           ↑                  ↑
        recv_buf          body_frag_start


                     recv_buffer that contains body only
                     ___________________________________

            |←------------------ body_frag_len ------------------→|
            |←--------------------- data len --------------------→|
       ---------------------------------------------------------------
</verbatim> </para>
<sect2 id="structhttp__response_1autotoc_md3">
<title>..header/body  |                         body                        |  body..</title>
<para>↑ recv_buf body_frag_start</para>
<para>body_frag_start &gt;= recv_buf body_frag_len = data_len - (body_frag_start - recv_buf) </para>
</sect2>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
